  "text": "The structure of a protein depends on its secondary structure. The percentage of the α-helices and β-sheets in the protein are important for the secondary structure of a protein. Secondary structure has an important role in protein structure, folding and its interaction [CITATION_1] . From the drug target dataset, the average of α-helices was found to be 69.73 and of β-sheet was 53.69. Therefore, the range of α-helices for a protein to be a drug target was set to be 60 to 80 and for β-sheets to be 40 to 60.",
